==Urdu==
===Etymology===
From Prakrit किअउं and Sanskrit कृतं (perf. part. neut. of कृ 'to do,')

===Postposition===
{{URchar|'''کا'''}} (kā) {{m}}

# [[of]]
# belonging to
#:{{URchar|عامل کی بیٹی}} "Aamil's daughter"
# concerning
# made of, consisting of

====Usage====
*{{URchar|'''کا'''}} is a possesive particle in Urdu to show relationships with people and things, and in many cases it can be translated as an ''apostrophe s'' as possession would be used in English. It is not used to show possesion by people of objects, the {{URchar|'''کے'''}} {{URchar|'''[[پاس]]'''}} construction is used for that. {{URchar|'''کا'''}} is the postposition of the genetive case in Urdū and Hindī, and, as such, is also frequently used as an adjective termination, e.g. sone-kī ghaṛī, 'a gold watch'; kāṭh-kā ghoṛā, 'a wooden horse'
<!--Rest of the Platts entry I didn't know what to do with or if it is still valid: "in the case of the pronouns of the first and second persons, kā takes the form rā; and in some dialects of Urdū rā is the genetive postposition of nouns as well as pronouns; while in others lā is found in place of kā and rā; cf. also kar, karā, ker, and kerā, which are rustic forms of kā)."-->
*The oblique form {{URchar|''کے''}} (ke) forms a large number of compound pospositions such as {{URchar|'''کے'''}} '''{{URchar|[[ساتھ]]}}''' (with), {{URchar|'''کے'''}} '''{{URchar|[[پیچھے]]}}''' (behind), etc.

====Inflection====
*Feminine: {{URchar|'''کی'''}} (kī)
*Oblique and plural: {{URchar|'''کے'''}} (ke)

